b'Savor the flavors of fall this weekend and check out this Mexican Rice Stuffed Butternut Squash recipe by @paulabendfeldt. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner

MEXICAN RICE STUFFED BUTTERNUT SQUASH 

Makes 2 main dishes or four side dish servings. Time: 60 min

Ingredients
1 medium butternut squash
1 1/2 tbsp Wellsley Farms Olive Oil
Salt & pepper to taste
1 cup Wellsley Farms Long Grain Brown Rice 
2 cups vegetable broth
1 can fire roasted diced tomatoes, drained 
\xc2\xbd cup canned black beans, drained
\xc2\xbd cup canned corn, drained
\xc2\xbe cup cilantro, chopped
\xc2\xbd tsp garlic powder
\xc2\xbd tsp onion powder
\xc2\xbd tsp chipotle chili powder
Feta
1 avocado, sliced

Instructions 
\xe2\x80\xa2 Preheat the oven to 425 F
\xe2\x80\xa2 With a knife, punch some holes in your butternut squash, then microwave for 4 min. Halve the butternut squash, scoop out the seeds, then arrange the halves on a baking tray, cut sides up
\xe2\x80\xa2 Brush with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake for about 45 min or until fork-tender. Remove from the oven and let cool
\xe2\x80\xa2 While the squash is baking, cook the brown rice according to package directions using the 2 cups of vegetable broth instead of water
\xe2\x80\xa2 In a large bowl, combine the rice, tomato, black beans, corn, \xc2\xbd cup of cilantro, garlic powder, and onion powder
\xe2\x80\xa2 Scoop out the squash flesh, leaving a 3/4-inch border. Reserve for another use 
\xe2\x80\xa2 Stuff the butternut squash with the Mexican rice filling, then return to the oven. Bake at 375 F about 10 min
\xe2\x80\xa2 Sprinkle fresh cilantro, feta cheese, and top with sliced avocado. Serve warm'

b'If there's ever been a year to get creative with your cooking for Thanksgiving, it's this one. Try out our Herbed Apple and Cranberry Cornbread Stuffing recipe for a little something extra at the dinner table. Full recipe below:

Ingredients: 

4 cups Wellsley Farms Mini Cornbread Loaves, crumbled 
Wellsley Farms Cooking Spray
1 Tbsp vegetable oil
\xc2\xbd cup chopped Wellsley Farms Yellow Onions
\xc2\xbd cup chopped celery
1 cup chopped Wellsley Farms Organic Granny Smith Apples
\xc2\xbd cup Wellsley Farms Pecan Halves
\xc2\xbe cup dried cranberries
1 tsp seasoned salt
1 tsp ground black pepper
2 tsp poultry seasoning
2 cups reduced-sodium organic chicken broth
2 eggs, beaten

Directions: 

1. Spread cornbread crumbs on a baking pan and set aside overnight to dry
2. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9" x 13" baking dish with cooking spray
3. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add onion, celery and apple. Saut\xc3\xa9 until tender, about 2 to 3 min
4. Stir in pecans, dried cranberries and seasoning. Saut\xc3\xa9 1 minute, then add chicken broth
5. Remove from heat, add cornbread and beaten eggs and toss gently to combine. Spoon mixture into prepared pan
6. Bake until center is completely heated'

b'Our pumpkin obsession is still going strong as we head into the holidays. Indulge in the flavors of the season with this Pumpkin Bread with Brown Sugar Streusel recipe from @faithjski. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner

Pumpkin Bread with Brown Sugar Streusel
Makes 2 Loaves 

Brown Sugar Streusel:
1 stick Wellsley Farms Unsalted Butter, melted
1 cup all-purpose flour
1/2 cup brown sugar
1/4 cup granulated sugar
1/2 tsp pumpkin pie spice
1/2 tsp cinnamon

Pumpkin Bread:
1 29 oz can of pumpkin puree
2 cup granulated sugar
1 cup brown sugar
1 cup vegetable oil
4 large eggs
2 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup milk
3 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
2 tsp baking soda
2 tsp cinnamon
1 tsp pumpkin pie spice
1 tsp salt

Maple Icing:
1 cup powdered sugar
1/2 cup Wellesley Farms 100% Pure Maple Syrup

INSTRUCTIONS:
Brown Sugar Streusel

1. In a small bowl, mix together all of the ingredients and place in the fridge while you make the pumpkin bread.

Pumpkin Bread

1.Preheat your oven to 325F. Spray the sides of a 9\xc3\x975 loaf pan with cooking spray and line with parchment paper if desired. This makes it easier to lift the bread out of the pan.
2. In a large bowl, whisk together the dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, salt) and set aside.
3. Using an electric mixer or a whisk, mix together the sugars, pumpkin, and oil in a larger bowl until well combined. Then mix in the eggs and vanilla.
4. Mix in half of the dry ingredients, then the milk, and then the rest of the dry ingredients until you get a smooth batter.
5. Pour it into the prepared pan and spread it out evenly.
6. Take the streusel out of the fridge and break it up using a knife or fork to create uniform crumbs.
7. Completely cover the top of the batter in streusel and bake for 1 hr and 25 minutes or until a toothpick in the middle comes out clean. 

Maple Icing
1. While the bread bakes, mix together the powdered sugar and maple syrup. 
2. Once the bread has cooled for 10 minutes, drizzle the glaze on top of the loaf. 

Let the pumpkin bread cool for about 10 minutes more and slice.'

b'Looking for an afternoon pick-me-up? Try this crepe recipe from @olya_timoshevich made with #WellsleyFarms baking staples. Brighten up your day and check out the full recipe below. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner 

You\xe2\x80\x99ll need: 

\xe2\x80\xa2 2 cups of Wellsley Farms Organic Milk 
\xe2\x80\xa2 3 eggs 
\xe2\x80\xa2 1.5 cups of flour 
\xe2\x80\xa2 1 tbsp vanilla extract 
\xe2\x80\xa2 1 stick of Wellsley Farms Organic Butter

1. Whisk together eggs and 1/2 of the milk, gradually adding the flour and the rest of the milk until your batter is smooth (or just mix together in a blender)
2. Using a scoop, put about 1/2 cup of batter into a non-stick pan and turn it sideways so the batter covers the whole surface of the pan
3. In about half a minute, turn the crepe over, then transfer to a plate and grease the crepe with butter
4. Repeat with each crepe (can use 2 pans at once to get it done faster)
5. Add your favorite toppings or fillings and enjoy!'

b'Busy days should mean relaxing nights. Spend less time cooking and more time recharging with this easy 3-Ingredient Spinach Dip Ravioli Lasagna from @chophappy, made with our #WellsleyFarms Jumbo Round Cheese Ravioli and Spinach Dip. This one will become an instant hit with the family. :face_savoring_food:  #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner 

Ingredients: 
1 bag Wellesley Farms Jumbo Ravioli 
1 container Wellesley Farms Spinach dip 
4 cups shredded mozzarella

Directions:
1. Place 2 baking dishes on the counter and add tablespoons of spinach dip into each
2. Spread around the bottom of the pan 
3. Add frozen raviolis to layer the bottom of both dishes
4. Evenly divide spinach dip on top of ravioli in each dish
5. Sprinkle 1/2 of the mozzarella on top of both dishes
6. Next, layer more ravioli in both dishes on top of spinach dip then sprinkle rest of cheese on top
7. Wrap both lasagnas up in tin foil (place one in the freezer for a later dinner) and place the other one in a preheated 400 degree oven for 30 min
8. Take tinfoil off and cook for 2 minutes to brown the cheese. Enjoy!'

b"Unique twists on classic favorites make for meals that the whole family will enjoy. We're loving this Smoked BLT recipe from @faithjski, and we have a feeling you will too! Check out the full recipe below. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesaleClub 

Ingredients (serves 4):

8 slices Wellsley Farms Thick Sliced Bacon
2-3 tomatoes on the vine
1 large Wellsley Farms Yellow Onion
\xc2\xbd cup Wellsley Farms Arugula
2 tbsp Wellsley Farms Extra Virgin Olive Oil
\xc2\xbc cup of mayonnaise
2-4 cloves of garlic 

Directions:

1. Prep your smoker with pellets or wood chips. Heat to 375 degrees
2. Arrange the bacon in a smoker pan or directly on the smoker grates and cook for 20-30 minutes, depending on your smoker and your preference 
3. Mince garlic and add to mayo to make aioli 
4. Prep veggies. Thinly slice the onion and slice the tomatoes 
5. Heat some olive oil in a pan on low heat. Add onions and cook until caramelized, about 10 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside
6. In the same pan the onions were in, toast the bread 
7. Assemble your sandwich! Spread mayo on both sides of the bread and layer starting with the tomatoes on the bottom, then add the bacon, arugula and caramelized onions 
8. Eat immediately!"

b'What better way to start the weekend than with a savory and easy dinner with family? This Honey Garlic Chicken and Broccoli recipe from @pbfingers is made with organic Wellsley Farms faves and is the perfect solution for your recipe-rotation boredom. Find the full recipe below! #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner 

Ingredients: \xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 3/4 cup chicken broth\xe2\x81\xa0 
\xe2\x80\xa2 1/3 cup soy sauce\xe2\x81\xa0 
\xe2\x80\xa2 1/3 cup Wellsley Farms Organic Honey\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 2 tbsp Wellsley Farms Organic Ketchup\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 2 tsp sriracha\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 5 cloves garlic, minced\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 1 tbsp rice vinegar\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x80\xa2 16 oz Wellsley Farms Organic Broccoli Florets (frozen)
\xe2\x80\xa2 3 tsp cornstarch
\xe2\x80\xa2 Optional: Sesame seeds and green onion for garnish; brown rice or cauliflower rice for serving\xe2\x81\xa0

Directions:
1. Whisk together the chicken broth through rice vinegar in a pressure cooker. Add the chicken thighs and stir to coat.
2. Cover, seal, and cook on manual high pressure for 8 minutes. Once done, turn the knob to quick -release the pressure and remove the lid.
3. Press off, remove the chicken and shred. Return the chicken to the pressure cooker and turn on the saute\xcc\x81 function.
4. Mix cornstarch into 1/4 cup of water in a small bowl and pour into the pressure cooker. Stir.
5. Add the broccoli and cook for about 15 minutes, stirring often, until broccoli has warmed and softened, and sauce has thickened a bit.
6. Spoon over brown rice or cauliflower rice, if desired, top with sesame seeds and enjoy!'

Chocolate Chip-Banana Muffins\xe2\x81\xa3

\xe2\x81\xa3

\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3

b"It's *technically* still summer, and this recipe for Steak with Onion Blue Cheese Sauce from @careeohhlinee is just the excuse you need to light up the grill. Find the full recipe below. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner 

Recipe: Steak with Onion Blue Cheese Sauce
Serves 2

Ingredients:
2 ribeye steaks (whole steaks)
2 tablespoons butter
Salt & pepper 
4 tablespoons butter
1 very large yellow onion, sliced
1 lb of baby bella mushrooms, sliced
1 cup heavy cream
1/2 cup Wellsley Farms Crumbled Blue Cheese

Preparation:
Salt and pepper both sides of the steaks.
Grill steaks in 2 tablespoons butter until medium rare.
Saut\xc3\xa9 onions in 4 tablespoons butter over high heat.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes, or until dark and caramelized.
While that cooks, saut\xc3\xa9 your mushrooms in a separate pan.
Reduce heat to simmer and pour in cream.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes, or until reduced by half.
Stir in blue cheese until melted and finish by adding the mushrooms.
Serve steaks with generous portion of sauce."

b"In need of some vegetarian-friendly recipes that will keep you full? Check out @pbfingers' Sweet Potato Grain Bowl below to change it up. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0

1/2 tablespoon olive oil\xe2\xa0\x80
1/2 large onion, chopped\xe2\xa0\x80
3/4 teaspoon dried thyme\xe2\xa0\x80
3/4 teaspoon garlic powder\xe2\xa0\x80
1 cup Wellsley Farms Organic Whole Grain Quinoa\xe2\xa0\x80
3 cups reduced sodium vegetable broth \xe2\xa0\x80
3 cups organic sweet potato (about 2 large sweet potatoes), peeled and cut into small cubes \xe2\xa0\x80
1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\xe2\xa0\x80
3 cups fresh Wellsley Farms Organic Spinach\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
1. Heat oil in a medium size pot over medium heat. Add onion, thyme and garlic powder and cook until onions are slightly soft, about 3 minutes. Add quinoa and allow to cook, stirring constantly, for approximately 2 minutes. 
2. Turn the heat to medium-high. Add broth, sweet potato, salt and pepper. Stir constantly and allow to simmer until broth is nearly completely dissolved and sweet potato begins to break down. Use a wooden spoon to help crush any large chunks of sweet potato so it becomes creamy and stir continuously. (This whole process should take 15-20 minutes.) It\xe2\x80\x99s okay if some chunks of sweet potato remain but you want it to be mostly creamy and dissolved and super-thick. 
3. Stir in Parmesan cheese. Add spinach and stir until leaves are wilted. Season to taste with additional salt and pepper. 
4. Divide into bowls and top with additional Parmesan cheese and enjoy!"

b'Looking to spend less time in the kitchen this weekend and more time with family? We love this quick and easy Chicken Alfredo Roll Up recipe from @arleenemendoza and the kids will too! Check out the full recipe below. #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesalePartner 

You\xe2\x80\x99ll need: 
8 lasagna noodles 
Shredded cooked chicken 
2 cups of spinach (chopped) 
Alfredo sauce (I made my own) 
2 cups mozzarella cheese

Directions: 
1.) Prepare pasta according to package. 
2.) While pasta is cooking, shred the chicken and chop the spinach.

b"Anyone else bored with their recipe rotation? We're loving this creative dinner from @ourtiny_nest. See below for her Sheet Pan Honey Mustard Pretzel Chicken with Roasted Broccoli and Potatoes recipe! #BJsWholesalePartner #BJsSmartSaver

Ingredients
8 chicken tenderloins
1 cup of honey mustard dressing
1 egg
2 cups of crushed pretzels (I used Wellsley Farms Pretzel Sticks)
3 cups broccoli florets
3 cups diced potatoes (Wellsley Farms)
Olive oil
Garlic powder
Salt/Pepper (to taste)

Directions
1.) Preheat oven to 400F.
2.) Line a large roasting pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
3.) On your prepared pan, place diced potatoes and chopped broccoli. Toss with olive oil, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
4.) Bake in oven for 10 minutes.
5.) While broccoli and potatoes are baking, pour honey mustard sauce in a medium bowl and whisk with 1 egg. This will be your wet mixture. In a shallow baking dish, pour the crushed pretzels. 
6.) Using one hand, pat the chicken with a paper towel and then dip in the honey mustard/egg mixture. Using your other hand (dry hand), dredge the chicken into the crushed pretzels.
7.) Remove the baking pan from the oven, flipping the potatoes and broccoli so you now brown the other side. Add the pretzel coated chicken tenders onto the aluminum foil lined pan and place in the oven for an additional 15-18 minutes or until chicken is cooked thoroughly.
8.) Serve with additional honey mustard sauce for dipping."

b"Who doesn't love a quick and easy recipe with only 3 steps?! Check out @aboutamom \xe2\x80\x98s 3-Ingredient Fish and Vegetable Foil Packets below. #BJsWholesaleClubPartner #BJsSmartSaver 
Here\xe2\x80\x99s the recipe: 
Fish and Vegetable Foil Packets (4-servings, prep time: 5 minutes, cooking time: 15 minutes, total time: 20 minutes)

Ingredients:

1 (16-ounce) bag Wellsley Farms Steam In Bag Mixed Vegetables

4 pieces Wellsley Farms Wild Caught Pacific Cod

2 Wellsley Farms Lemons, divided

3 tablespoons olive oil, divided

\xc2\xbd teaspoon salt, divided

\xc2\xbd teaspoon pepper, divided

\xc2\xbd teaspoon garlic powder, divided 
You will need 4 (16x12 inch) sheets of aluminum foil. 
Directions:

Thaw cod according to package directions. Vegetables can remain frozen, until ready to use.

Preheat oven to 400\xc2\xb0F.

Slice one lemon into thin slices. Remaining lemon will be used for juice.

Arrange foil sheets on a work surface.

Divide vegetables into 4 portions and place onto middle of foil sheet. Sprinkle with half of the salt and pepper. Drizzle with small amount of olive oil and lemon juice.

Top each one with a piece of cod. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Drizzle equally with remaining olive oil and lemon juice. Top each piece of fish with lemon slices.

Add a few drops of water to each piece of foil to help create steam. Fold edges together and seal foil packets tightly.

Cook on rimmed baking sheet for 13-15 minutes.

Carefully, open one packet to make sure fish is cooked through. If not, re-seal and continue to bake until done. Serve right away, opening packets at the table."

b'Looking for a quick, flavorful lunch? Add spicy nut butter sauce to butternut squash noodles and top it with vegetables to take this dish to the next level. :steaming_bowl:
Butternut Squash Noodles with Spicy Almond Sauce 
INGREDIENTS 
1/2 cup almond butter 
1/4 cup soy sauce 
2 Tbsp Brown Sugar 
2 Tbsp lime juice 
1 Tbsp hot chili sauce
1 Tbsp fresh ginger, peeled and finely chopped 
1 clove garlic, peeled and finely chopped 
16 oz butternut squash noodles 
1 cup cucumber, thinly sliced 
1/2 large bell pepper, chopped 
3 Scallions, sliced 
DIRECTIONS 
1. Mix almond butter, soy sauce, brown sugar, lime juice, chili sauce, ginger and garlic together. Set aside. 
2. Bring a pot of water to boil. Add the butternut squash noodles and cook for 3-4 minutes. Drain. 
3. Toss the noodles with the almond sauce. Divide among 4 bowls. 
4. Top with vegetables and serve.'

b'Try this \xe2\x80\x9cegg-ceptional\xe2\x80\x9d traditional Greek Egg and Lemon Soup. It\xe2\x80\x99s perfect for those chilly nights.
Greek Egg and Lemon Soup 
INGREDIENTS 
4 oz spaghetti or angel hair pasta
2 qt box Wellsley Farms Organic Chicken Broth 
3 Wellsley Farms Extra Large Grade A Brown Eggs, separated 
6 Tbsp. Lemon juice, (fresh or packaged) 
2 cups chopped Wellsley Farms Rotisserie Chicken 
DIRECTIONS 
1. Place pasta in large, re-sealable plastic bag and break into tiny pieces. (A rubber mallet or the smooth side of a meat tenderizer works well for this.) 2. Bring chicken broth to a boil in a large saucepan. Add pasta pieces and cook until tender, about 5 min. Turn off heat. 
3. Whisk egg whites in a medium mixing bowl until just foamy, about 3 min. Add yolks to bowl and whisk 2 min. 
4. While whisking, slowly pour lemon juice into bowl with eggs. 
5. Still whisking, slowly pour 3 cups of strained, hot broth into bowl a little at a time. 
6. With stove on low, slowly add egg mixture to reserved ingredients in saucepan, stirring constantly as you pour. 
7. Add chicken to pan and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, about 5 min. Serve immediately.'

b'Try this flavorful Skillet Chicken with Olives and Lemon dish that uses our #WellsleyFarms olives and olive oil. 
Skillet Chicken with Olives and Lemon 
INGREDIENTS
2 lemons 
1/4 cup olive oil 
6 boneless, skinless chicken thighs 
2 Tbsp all-purpose flour 
kosher salt and freshly cracked black pepper 
1/2 medium yellow onion, chopped 
1 clove garlic, finely minced 
1 1/2 cups chicken broth 
3/4 cup green olives 
2 Tbsp butter 
2 Tbsp parsley, chopped 
DIRECTIONS
1. Juice one lemon and set juice aside. Slice remaining lemon into 1/4" slices. 
2. Bring a skillet to medium-high heat and add 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add the lemon slices and sear until browned, 3-5 minutes on each side. Transfer to a plate. 
3. Season the chicken thighs with salt and black pepper and dust with flour, shaking off the excess. Add 2 tablespoons of olive oil to the hot pan and brown chicken until golden, about 5 minutes each side. Brown in 2 batches if necessary, to not crowd the chicken in the pan. Transfer to a plate. 
4. Add the remaining olive oil to the pan and cook onion until softened. Add the minced garlic, stirring constantly for about 30 seconds or until fragrant. 
5. Add the broth, olives and reserved lemon juice. Transfer the reserved chicken, lemons and any juices from the platter back into the pan. Simmer over medium-high heat until the broth is reduced by half, about 5 minutes. 
6. Add the butter and parsley and cook for another minute. Serve over rice or couscous. 
DIRECTIONS'

b'Why eat ordinary when you can add some salsa to your salmon? Infused with fruits and veggies, this salsa kicks things up a notch. 
Salmon with Cucumber Salsa 
INGREDIENTS
1/2 Cucumber, peeled, quartered and thinly sliced
1 cup Tomatoes, quartered
1/2 Yellow Bell Pepper, cut in 1" strips
2 Tbsp. finely chopped Red Onion
1 tsp. Parsley
1 tsp. Lime juice
1 1/2 tsp. Extra Virgin Olive Oil, divided
1 tsp. Clover Honey
1/2 tsp. Crushed Red Pepper
Approx. 1 tsp. Sea Salt
10 oz. fresh Farm-Raised Salmon Fillet
Approx. 1/4 tsp. Black Pepper
Fresh Lime wedges (for garnish)
DIRECTIONS
1. Gently toss together cucumber, tomatoes, bell pepper and red onion in medium bowl.
2. In small bowl whisk together lime juice, 1 tsp. of oil, honey, red pepper flakes, parsley and \xc2\xbd tsp. of salt.
3. Pour dressing over cucumber salsa, toss and set aside.
4. Slice salmon into four 5-oz. fillets approximately 1" thick. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
5. Heat remaining oil in large nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat. Carefully add fish to pan.
6. Cook 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, until 145\xc2\xba on food thermometer at thickest spot.
7. Transfer to dinner plates. Top each fillet with \xc2\xbc of the salsa and garnish with lime wedges.
8. Serve hot with steamed broccoli florets.'

b'Chia is considered an ancient grain and is the Mayan word for \xe2\x80\x9cstrength,\xe2\x80\x9d which hints at its popularity as a superfood. Chia Oatmeal Pancakes can help pack that extra-filling punch to kick up your day. :pancakes:

Chia Oatmeal Pancakes
IGREDIENTS
1 1/4 cups flour 
1 cup quick cooking oats 
2 Tbsp. Sugar 
2 tsp Baking powder 
1/2 tsp Salt 
1 1/2 cups milk 
2 eggs 
4 Tbsp melted butter 
2 tsp vanilla extract 
2 Tbsp chia seeds 
DIRECTIONS
1. Place flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt in a blender and pulse until fine. 
2. Add milk, eggs, butter, vanilla and chia seeds. Blend on low just until remaining ingredients are incorporated. 
3. Heat a frying pan or griddle to medium-high heat. 
4. Pour 1/4 cup of batter into pan for each pancake. Brown on both sides. 
5. Serve hot.'
